<emphasis box="[151,263,1472,1498]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">fodincana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[278,363,1472,1498]" captionStart="FIGURES 38–42" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[186,1380,189,1897]" captionTargetId="figure-17@19.[186,1402,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 38–42. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) fodincana new species ex Coracina papuensis oriomo. 38, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 39, male genitalia, dorsal view. 40, male mesosome, ventral view. 41, male paramere, dorsal view. 42, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825573" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825573/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 42</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="17" lastPageNumber="18" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1112,2039]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,480,1507,1534]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
Description. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[351,473,1507,1534]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Both sexes</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Head rounded trapezoidal (
<figureCitation box="[787,869,1508,1534]" captionStart="FIGURES 31–35" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[185,1376,206,1889]" captionTargetId="figure-23@16.[179,1408,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 31–35. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) wandoensis new species ex Coracina novaehollandiae melanops. 31, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 32, male genitalia, dorsal view. 33, male mesosome, ventral view. 34, male paramere, dorsal view. 35, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825569" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825569/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
), lateral margins of preantennal head convex, frons flattened. Marginal carina broad, narrowing anterior to 
<emphasis box="[788,844,1544,1570]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">dsms</emphasis>
, deeply displaced and widened at osculum. Ventral anterior plate rounded, with concave anterior margin and sinuous lateral margins. Head chaetotaxy as in 
<figureCitation box="[1348,1432,1580,1606]" captionStart="FIGURES 31–35" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[185,1376,206,1889]" captionTargetId="figure-23@16.[179,1408,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 31–35. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) wandoensis new species ex Coracina novaehollandiae melanops. 31, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 32, male genitalia, dorsal view. 33, male mesosome, ventral view. 34, male paramere, dorsal view. 35, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825569" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825569/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
. Preantennal nodi wide, bulging. Pre- and post-ocular nodi large, connected dorsally by broad ocular band. Marginal temporal carina slender. Gular plate triangular, lateral margins slightly convex. Thoracic and abdominal segments as in 
<figureCitation box="[208,336,1688,1714]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–30" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[262,1328,195,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-17@15.[238,1349,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 29–30. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) wandoensis new species ex Coracina novaehollandiae melanops. 29, male habitus, dorsal and ventral views. 30, female habitus, dorsal and ventral views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825567" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825567/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Figs 29–30</figureCitation>
. Base pigmentation translucently pale yellow; head nodi, gular plate, proepimera, and metepisterna dark brown; margins of antennal sockets, mandibular framework, sternal plate IV–VI and subgenital plates medium brown; head carinae yellowish.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1112,2039]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,265,1795,1822]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Male.</emphasis>
Thoracic and abdominal chaetotaxy as in 
<figureCitation box="[732,813,1796,1822]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–30" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[262,1328,195,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-17@15.[238,1349,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 29–30. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) wandoensis new species ex Coracina novaehollandiae melanops. 29, male habitus, dorsal and ventral views. 30, female habitus, dorsal and ventral views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825567" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825567/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
; tergopleurite IV with 2 
<emphasis box="[1083,1105,1797,1822]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">ss</emphasis>
and tergopleurites V–VI with 3 
<emphasis box="[173,195,1833,1858]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">ss</emphasis>
on each side; sternite III with 1 
<emphasis box="[568,598,1833,1858]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">sts</emphasis>
on each side. Basal apodeme rounded, with concave lateral margins (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 31–35" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[185,1376,206,1889]" captionTargetId="figure-23@16.[179,1408,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 31–35. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) wandoensis new species ex Coracina novaehollandiae melanops. 31, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 32, male genitalia, dorsal view. 33, male mesosome, ventral view. 34, male paramere, dorsal view. 35, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825569" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825569/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
). Proximal mesosome with antero-lateral extensions (
<figureCitation box="[778,860,1868,1894]" captionStart="FIGURES 31–35" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[185,1376,206,1889]" captionTargetId="figure-23@16.[179,1408,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 31–35. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) wandoensis new species ex Coracina novaehollandiae melanops. 31, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 32, male genitalia, dorsal view. 33, male mesosome, ventral view. 34, male paramere, dorsal view. 35, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825569" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825569/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 33</figureCitation>
), anterior margin deeply concave. Mesosomal lobes divergent distally. Distal margin of mesosome concave, but median section bulging. Gonopore with slightly hooked antero-lateral extensions. Dorsal fringe not tilted posteriorly. Chaetotaxy: 1 ventral 
<emphasis box="[1089,1161,1941,1966]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">gpmes</emphasis>
microsetae on each side lateral to distal gonopore; 2 
<emphasis box="[467,532,1976,2002]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">lpmes</emphasis>
sensilla on each side on mesosomal lobes; 1 dorsal 
<emphasis box="[1117,1175,1977,2002]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">ames</emphasis>
microseta on each side posterior to dorsal fringe. Parameres and 
<emphasis box="[614,688,2012,2038]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">pst1–2</emphasis>
as in 
<figureCitation box="[755,837,2012,2038]" captionStart="FIGURES 31–35" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[185,1376,206,1889]" captionTargetId="figure-23@16.[179,1408,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 31–35. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) wandoensis new species ex Coracina novaehollandiae melanops. 31, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 32, male genitalia, dorsal view. 33, male mesosome, ventral view. 34, male paramere, dorsal view. 35, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825569" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825569/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
. Measurements as in 
<tableCitation box="[1077,1161,2012,2038]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="47.[151,239,457,483]" captionText="TABLE 1. Measurements (in mm) of species treated in this paper. Abbreviations used: TL = total length; HL = head length (along midline); HW = head width (at temples); PRW = prothorax width; PTW = pterothorax width; AW = abdominal width (at segment V). Note: many specimens had distorted abdomens, as noted below; consequently, the TL of many specimens could not be measured. Mean values are given in parentheses only where 10 or more individuals were measured. N = number of specimens examined." pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
