<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,150,573]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,293,150,177]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Female.</emphasis>
Thoracic and abdominal chaetotaxy as in 
<figureCitation box="[759,841,150,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–30" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[262,1328,195,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-17@15.[238,1349,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 29–30. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) wandoensis new species ex Coracina novaehollandiae melanops. 29, male habitus, dorsal and ventral views. 30, female habitus, dorsal and ventral views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825567" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825567/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
; female sternite III with 2 
<emphasis box="[1132,1162,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">sts</emphasis>
on each side. Subgenital plate as in 
<figureCitation box="[268,349,186,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 31–35" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[185,1376,206,1889]" captionTargetId="figure-23@16.[179,1408,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 31–35. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) wandoensis new species ex Coracina novaehollandiae melanops. 31, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 32, male genitalia, dorsal view. 33, male mesosome, ventral view. 34, male paramere, dorsal view. 35, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825569" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825569/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 35</figureCitation>
, lateral margins concave in distal section, distal margin rounded. Vulval margin bulging medianly, with 2–3 short, slender 
<emphasis box="[411,455,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">vms</emphasis>
and 1 short, thorn-like 
<emphasis box="[712,746,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">vss</emphasis>
on each side; 4–6 slender 
<emphasis box="[1038,1075,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">vos</emphasis>
on each side of subgenital plate; distal 2 
<emphasis box="[240,277,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">vos</emphasis>
distal to 
<emphasis box="[381,415,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">vss</emphasis>
, substantially longer than 
<emphasis box="[711,755,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">vms</emphasis>
. Measurements as in 
<tableCitation box="[998,1081,258,284]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="47.[151,239,457,483]" captionText="TABLE 1. Measurements (in mm) of species treated in this paper. Abbreviations used: TL = total length; HL = head length (along midline); HW = head width (at temples); PRW = prothorax width; PTW = pterothorax width; AW = abdominal width (at segment V). Note: many specimens had distorted abdomens, as noted below; consequently, the TL of many specimens could not be measured. Mean values are given in parentheses only where 10 or more individuals were measured. N = number of specimens examined." pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
